  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> into discs (as finely as you can!)</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato discs</strong> to a baking tray with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: If you're cooking for 4, use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through and starting to crisp</p><p>Tip: Give them a gentle mix up half way through!</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (as finely as you can!)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 3/4 of the <strong>chopped onion</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained black beans</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chipotle paste</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [80ml]</span> <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until a thick sauce remains</p><p>Once thickened, mash gently – these are your <strong>refried beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2152-Step-4-x200.jpg",
